webpackJsonp([0xb70c466e0d0b],{851:function(e,a){e.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"weiran.co",author:"Weiran Zhang"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/weiran/git/weiran/weiran.co/src/pages/blog/2013/3/hackers-a-hacker-news-app-for-iphone/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>Today I released my new iPhone app, <a href="http://weiranzhang.com/hackers">Hackers</a>, which I’ve been working on for the past few months.</p>\n<p>Hackers is an iPhone app designed for reading Hacker News on the go. I took a content first approach to the design which has resulted in a minimalist style. It takes some getting used to, especially not having separators between table cells, but with distinctive headers I didn’t feel it was necessary.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/a53c871f-3e35-4aaf-83e2-1c1ec8542cba-bcc7becba53f5b12cec079e775173dfc-c3b2a.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 61.7%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="a53c871f 3e35 4aaf 83e2 1c1ec8542cba"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/a53c871f-3e35-4aaf-83e2-1c1ec8542cba-bcc7becba53f5b12cec079e775173dfc-fb8a0.png"\n        srcset="/static/a53c871f-3e35-4aaf-83e2-1c1ec8542cba-bcc7becba53f5b12cec079e775173dfc-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/a53c871f-3e35-4aaf-83e2-1c1ec8542cba-bcc7becba53f5b12cec079e775173dfc-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/a53c871f-3e35-4aaf-83e2-1c1ec8542cba-bcc7becba53f5b12cec079e775173dfc-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/a53c871f-3e35-4aaf-83e2-1c1ec8542cba-bcc7becba53f5b12cec079e775173dfc-526de.png 885w,\n/static/a53c871f-3e35-4aaf-83e2-1c1ec8542cba-bcc7becba53f5b12cec079e775173dfc-c3b2a.png 1000w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Hackers focuses on the most common way of reading Hacker News on an iPhone, during travelling or while waiting in queues. You may not have time to read a whole article and all the comments, but you have enough to skim the top posts and their top comments.</p>\n<h2>Open source</h2>\n<p>I’ve released Hackers as an <a href="https://github.com/weiran/Hackers">open source project on GitHub</a>. Please fork it, play around, and install it on your iPhone for free if you have developer account.</p>\n<p>If you prefer the convenience of having automatic updates, you can buy Hackers on the App Store for £1.49 ($1.99):</p>\n<p><a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/hackers-hacker-news-reading/id603503901">\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/a4520d57-ab05-4360-8007-0f0c3813e512-8ee9e8ac3edf25f8c212933b2bb26aac-e3c83.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 135px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 29.629629629629626%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="a4520d57 ab05 4360 8007 0f0c3813e512"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/a4520d57-ab05-4360-8007-0f0c3813e512-8ee9e8ac3edf25f8c212933b2bb26aac-e3c83.png"\n        srcset="/static/a4520d57-ab05-4360-8007-0f0c3813e512-8ee9e8ac3edf25f8c212933b2bb26aac-e3c83.png 135w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 135px) 100vw, 135px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </a></p>\n<p>Hopefully people can learn from my mistakes and particular ways I’ve implemented features. At the least it’s an entry into the crazy world of AutoLayout with Storyboards.</p>\n<h2>Future work</h2>\n<p>I will be continually working on Hackers, there are several features I’d like for the next version as well as iPad support. If you’d like to suggest something, create a new issue on GitHub, get in touch via Twitter: <a href="https://twitter.com/weiran">@weiran</a>, or implement it yourself and send me a pull request.</p>',frontmatter:{title:"Hackers - a Hacker News app for iPhone",date:"March 01, 2013",passthroughUrl:null}}},pathContext:{slug:"/blog/2013/3/hackers-a-hacker-news-app-for-iphone/",previous:{fields:{slug:"/blog/2013/3/strip-launches-uk-beta/"},frontmatter:{title:"Strip launches UK beta",passthroughUrl:"http://thenextweb.com/uk/2013/03/01/stripe-uk-europe-launch/"}},next:{fields:{slug:"/blog/2013/3/the-shawshank-redemption-a-powerful-lesson/"},frontmatter:{title:"'The Shawshank Redemption': A powerful lesson",passthroughUrl:"http://statspotting.com/a-lesson-from-the-shawshank-redemption/"}}}}}});
